<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> as it was • as it were</xh5><p> <i>as it was—</i>1. just the way it was <i>(usually said of goods that may be slightly damaged, without guarantee, etc.): </i>The family bought the estate <u>as it was</u>: ruined, discredited, its buildings in bad condition. 2. in the actual state of affairs; as the situation was: If we had been able to find a taxi, we should have caught the train. <u>As it was</u> we were late.</p><p> <i>as it were—</i>in a way; so to speak: He was, <u>as it were</u>, the missing link between the artist and the commercial public.</p> </entry>
